Definition: A nervous system cancer that is located in the peripheral nervous system.

Name: nervous system hibernoma
Definition: A breast adenocarcinoma that is characterized as a well-differentiated invasive carcinoma with regular cells arranged in well-defined tubules (typically one layer thick) surrounded by an abundant fibrohyaline stroma.
